			</div> <!-- .et_pb_section --><div class="et_pb_section et_pb_section_parallax  et_pb_section_10 et_pb_with_background et_section_regular">
				
				
					
					<div class=" et_pb_row et_pb_row_15 et_pb_row_fullwidth">
				
				<div class="et_pb_column et_pb_column_4_4  et_pb_column_25">
				
				<div class="et_pb_number_counter et_pb_module et_pb_bg_layout_dark  et_pb_number_counter_0" data-number-value="193833342">
				<div class="percent" style="color:#85d383"><p><span class="percent-value"></span></p></div>
				<h3>Sent Messages Over Matrix</h3>
			</div><!-- .et_pb_number_counter -->
			</div> <!-- .et_pb_column -->
					
			</div> <!-- .et_pb_row -->
				
			</div> <!-- .et_pb_section --><div class="et_pb_section  et_pb_section_11 et_section_regular">
				
				
					
					<div class=" et_pb_row et_pb_row_16">
				
				<div class="et_pb_column et_pb_column_4_4  et_pb_column_26">
				
				<div class="et_pb_text et_pb_module et_pb_bg_layout_light et_pb_text_align_center  et_pb_text_11">
				
<p>Encryption and Privacy in Matrix</p>

			</div> <!-- .et_pb_text --><div class="et_pb_text et_pb_module et_pb_bg_layout_light et_pb_text_align_left  et_pb_text_12">
				
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Privacy is particularly critical for a decentralized network like Matrix, where user data is replicated over all the servers participating in a room and so must be protected.Â </span>Matrix provides state of the art end-to-end encryption <strong>in beta</strong>Â using theÂ <a href="../../git/olm">Olm</a>Â and <a href="../../docs/spec/megolm.html">Megolm</a>Â cryptographic ratchets, and ensuring that only explicitly authorized devices can participate in a conversation.</p>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Based on the Double Ratchet Algorithm popularised by Signal</span></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Independently assessed by NCC Group &#8211; read ourÂ <a href="http://bit.ly/2hohFDu">blog post</a>Â and the <a href="https://nccgroup.trust/us/our-research/matrix-olm-cryptographic-review">public report</a>Â here!</span></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Provides 1:1 encrypted channels between pairs of devices via the Olm double ratchet</span></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Supports group chats with hundreds of devices via the new Megolm shared ratchet, with either perfect forward secrecy <em>or</em>Â the ability to decrypt conversation history on new devices.</span></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Supports multiple devices, tracking verification trust per-device to help spot interception.</span></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Independent implementation released under the Apache License</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Currently any apps built on <a href="https://github.com/matrix-org/matrix-js-sdk">matrix-js-sdk</a>, <a href="https://github.com/matrix-org/matrix-ios-sdk">matrix-ios-sdk</a>Â or <a href="https://github.com/matrix-org/matrix-android-sdk">matrix-android-sdk</a>Â support encryption, which is in beta as of March 2017. Â The libolm library itself is considered stable however.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">For more information about Matrix&#8217;s encryption, you can check out our main-track talk at <a href="https://fosdem.org/2017/schedule/event/encrypting_matrix">FOSDEM 2017</a>.</span></p>

			</div> <!-- .et_pb_text -->
			</div> <!-- .et_pb_column -->
					
			</div> <!-- .et_pb_row --><div class=" et_pb_row et_pb_row_17 et_pb_row_fullwidth">
				
				<div class="et_pb_column et_pb_column_1_4  et_pb_column_27 et_pb_column_empty">
				
				
			</div> <!-- .et_pb_column --><div class="et_pb_column et_pb_column_1_4  et_pb_column_28">
				
				<div class="et_pb_module et-waypoint et_pb_image et_pb_animation_left et_pb_image_9 et_always_center_on_mobile">
				<a href="https://nccgroup.trust"><img src="https://matrix.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/ncc-group-plc-logo.jpg" alt="" />
			</a>
			</div>
			</div> <!-- .et_pb_column --><div class="et_pb_column et_pb_column_1_4  et_pb_column_29">
				
				<div class="et_pb_button_module_wrapper et_pb_module et_pb_button_alignment_center">
